  <amendments/>
  <summary>10/4/2001--Introduced.
Declares that, in the quest to identify, locate, and bring to justice the perpetrators and sponsors of the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks on the United States, the civil rights and liberties of all Americans, including Sikh-Americans, should be protected.Condemns bigotry and acts of violence or discrimination against any Americans, including Sikh-Americans.Calls upon local and Federal law enforcement authorities to: (1) work to prevent hate crimes against all Americans; and (2) prosecute to the fullest extent of the law all those who commit hate crimes.</summary>
